{
  "stem": "13395.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother went every day to the city, to Katowice, to Konig city-- which now was changed again, the names, into German-- where more Jews were living, and was searching for some news.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Maybe somebody came back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maybe somebody brought some news.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nobody-- those-- these men disappeared.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I cannot describe the nights that I sat with my mother crying, praying, wondering what's going to happen and what's going to be and how long we're going to stay.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A terrible thing happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "One day, she-- we still had-- she had some money, and Jews were not allowed to have any money.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So she packed it all and put it-- in Europe you had an oven-- like we have now electric, you had one that you made a fire to bake your bread in the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she hid it-- hid the money in the oven.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in the whole commotion in being so upset and distraught as she was, she wanted to bake some bread, since we couldn't buy anything.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And she made fire in the oven, and suddenly remembered that all her money was there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Everything we had was there in flames.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] She took it out, as burned as it was that little pack-- package with the money, the bill-- paper bills.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But she had her mind in the right place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She wrapped it up in cotton, and she sent it to Berlin in the national German bank with the name Steinitz, Alfreda Steinitz.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They had no idea that they were dealing with a Jew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "She wrote them that she inadvertently burned the money.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There was a fire in the house.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They bought the story, and they sent us back the money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They gave us-- they could see the numbers, and they sent back the money.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
